{"word":"σάος","slug":"σάος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σάος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>as Posit., found only in the <a href='S:contracted, contraction'>contr.</a> form <el>σῶς, σᾶ</el>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <el>σαώτερος</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>σαώτερον</el>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>\n"}]}